 {"id":"bd-1c6.12","title":"Example: Syntax highlighting demonstration","description":"# Example: Syntax Highlighting Demonstration

## Purpose

Demonstrate the syntax highlighting system in action. This example shows users how to:
1. Enable syntax highlighting on a text buffer
2. Switch between themes
3. Display highlighted code in the terminal

This is the showcase example that proves the syntax highlighting epic delivers user value.

## Code Structure

Create `examples/11_highlighting.rs`:

```rust
//\! Example 11: Syntax Highlighting
//\!
//\! This example demonstrates the syntax highlighting system by:
//\! 1. Loading and displaying Rust source code with syntax colors
//\! 2. Allowing theme switching with keyboard shortcuts
//\! 3. Showing incremental highlighting updates
//\!
//\! Run with: cargo run --example 11_highlighting
//\! Controls:
//\!   1-4: Switch themes (Dark, Light, Solarized, High Contrast)
//\!   q: Quit

use opentui::{
    Renderer, OptimizedBuffer, Rgba, Style,
    highlight::{HighlightedBuffer, Theme, RustTokenizer},
    text::TextBuffer,
    input::{KeyCode, KeyEvent},
};
use std::io;
use tracing::info;

const SAMPLE_CODE: &str = r#"
/// Calculate the factorial of a number.
fn factorial(n: u64) -> u64 {
    match n {
        0 | 1 => 1,
        _ => n * factorial(n - 1),
    }
}

fn main() {
    let numbers = [5, 10, 15];
    for n in numbers {
        println\!("factorial({n}) = {}", factorial(n));
    }
}
"#;

fn main() -> io::Result<()> {
    // Setup logging for debugging
    let _ = tracing_subscriber::fmt()
        .with_max_level(tracing::Level::INFO)
        .try_init();

    info\!("Starting syntax highlighting example");

    // Create renderer
    let mut renderer = Renderer::new(80, 24)?;
    let (width, height) = renderer.size();

    // Create highlighted buffer
    let text_buffer = TextBuffer::from_str(SAMPLE_CODE);
    let mut highlighted = HighlightedBuffer::new(text_buffer)
        .with_tokenizer(Box::new(RustTokenizer::new()))
        .with_theme(Theme::dark());
    highlighted.update_highlighting();

    let themes = [
        ("Dark", Theme::dark()),
        ("Light", Theme::light()),
        ("Solarized", Theme::solarized_dark()),
        ("High Contrast", Theme::high_contrast()),
    ];
    let mut current_theme = 0;

    loop {
        // Clear and draw
        let buffer = renderer.buffer();
        buffer.clear(highlighted.theme().background());

        // Draw title bar
        buffer.draw_text(
            2, 0,
            &format\!("Syntax Highlighting Demo - Theme: {} (press 1-4 to switch, q to quit)",
                     themes[current_theme].0),
            Style::fg(Rgba::from_hex("#888888").unwrap()),
        );

        // Draw highlighted code
        for (line_idx, line_y) in (0..highlighted.line_count()).zip(2..height - 1) {
            let styled_segments = highlighted.styled_line(line_idx);
            let mut x = 2u32;

            for segment in styled_segments {
                buffer.draw_text(x, line_y as u32, &segment.text, segment.style);
                x += segment.text.len() as u32;
            }
        }

        renderer.present()?;

        // Handle input
        if let Some(event) = renderer.poll_event(std::time::Duration::from_millis(100))? {
            match event.key {
                KeyEvent::Char('q') => break,
                KeyEvent::Char('1') => {
                    current_theme = 0;
                    highlighted.set_theme(themes[0].1.clone());
                    info\!(theme = themes[0].0, "Theme switched");
                }
                KeyEvent::Char('2') => {
                    current_theme = 1;
                    highlighted.set_theme(themes[1].1.clone());
                    info\!(theme = themes[1].0, "Theme switched");
                }
                KeyEvent::Char('3') => {
                    current_theme = 2;
                    highlighted.set_theme(themes[2].1.clone());
                    info\!(theme = themes[2].0, "Theme switched");
                }
                KeyEvent::Char('4') => {
                    current_theme = 3;
                    highlighted.set_theme(themes[3].1.clone());
                    info\!(theme = themes[3].0, "Theme switched");
                }
                _ => {}
            }
        }
    }

    info\!("Example completed");
    Ok(())
}
```

## Key Concepts Demonstrated

1. **HighlightedBuffer usage** - How to wrap TextBuffer with highlighting
2. **Theme switching** - Runtime theme changes without re-tokenization
3. **Styled segments** - Rendering highlighted text to buffer
4. **Tokenizer selection** - Choosing the right tokenizer for file type
5. **Interactive demo** - Keyboard controls for theme switching

## Dependencies

This example depends on:
- bd-2x0.10 (Highlighting integration)
- bd-2x0.3 (Theme system)
- bd-2x0.4 (Rust tokenizer)

